div1.p:
Prisoner's defence. I went one morning to Mr. Wilson's wharf;
James Webb
came and asked meto go and clean his pigs; he had two sows and some pigs; I was to get some wash for them, and I was to go to Briley's for him; he told me to take that bag of nails; I refused to take them without a direction; he gave me the direction, and he told me he would come close by me; I have carried parcels of nails for him a great many times.
